Legal Provisions, Guidelines, and Procedures

INSTRUCTIONS FOR APPLICATION OF A NEW PREMISE LICENSE

When applying for a New premise license:

  • Log into the PPB’s practice portal through practice.pharmacyboardkenya.org
  • Sign in using your registration or enrollment number and password
  • Once logged in, click on New Facility on the dashboard then fill in the details of the New premise, attach E-citizen name search of the business and current medical council license if it is a hospital
  • Submit the application and wait for communication of review process from the Board.
  • If approved, follow the instructions and complete the application as per the premise type applied for and submit for payment
  • Once on the payment page, follow the instructions on payment and download your receipt after successful submission of payment
  • If approved, the Regional PPB office will contact the applicant for inspection of the premise
  • Final review process will happen after the inspection.
  • 0nce approved, the applicant should download and print the license for purposes of conspicuously displaying in the premises

INSTRUCTIONS FOR RENEWAL OF A PREMISE LICENSE AS A SUPERINTENDENT

When applying for a license as a superintendent:

  • Log into the PPB’s practice portal through practice.pharmacyboardkenya.org
  • Sign in using your registration or enrollment number and password
  • Once logged in, click on “Renewal” on the dashboard then “New renewal application”
  • Write the name of the premise and wait for a drop-down list to appear from the database and choose the premise from the list
  • Choose “YES” for superintendent
  • If the premise type is Retail or Wholesale, add the name of the director at the bottom and submit
  • If the premise is a Hospital, attach the current year’s medical council license, add the name of the director at the bottom and submit for payment
  • If the premise is a Manufacturer, attach the current GMP certificate from PPB, add the name of the director at the bottom and submit for payment
  • Once on the payment page, follow the instructions on payment and download your receipt and wait for communication from the Board on the review process.

INSTRUCTIONS FOR RENEWAL OF A PRACTICE LICENSE AS A NON-SUPERINTENDENT

When applying for a license as a non-superintendent:

  • Log into the PPB’s practice portal through practice.pharmacyboardkenya.org
  • Sign in using your registration or enrollment number and password
  • Once logged in, click on Renewal on the dashboard then New renewal application
  • Write the name of the premise and wait for a drop down to appear from the database and choose the premise from the list
  • Choose “NO” for superintendent and submit for payment
  • Once on the payment page, follow the instructions on payment and download your receipt and wait for communication from the Board on the review process.
  • Note that the superintendent has to apply first and the premise license approved before any other person can be approved

INSTRUCTIONS FOR VARATION OF AN ISSUED LICENSE

When applying for a variation of an issued license:

  • Log into the PPB’s practice portal through practice.pharmacyboardkenya.org
  • Sign in using your registration or enrollment number and password
  • Once logged in, click on Variation on the dashboard
  • Choose the type of variation from the drop down, write the reason(s) for variation and attach the appropriate evidence
  • Submit and pay if payment is required and wait for communication from the Board on the review process.

INSTRUCTIONS FOR RENEWAL OF A PRACTICE LICENSE AS A NON-SUPERINTENDENT

When applying for a license as a non-superintendent:

  • Log into the PPB’s practice portal through practice.pharmacyboardkenya.org
  • Sign in using your registration or enrollment number and password
  • Once logged in, click on Renewal on the dashboard then New renewal application
  • Write the name of the premise and wait for a drop down to appear from the database and choose the premise from the list
  • Choose “NO” for superintendent and submit for payment
  • Once on the payment page, follow the instructions on payment and download your receipt and wait for communication from the Board on the review process.
  • Note that the superintendent has to apply first and the premise license approved before any other person can be approved

INSTRUCTIONS FOR VARATION OF AN ISSUED LICENSE

When applying for a variation of an issued license:

  • Log into the PPB’s practice portal through practice.pharmacyboardkenya.org
  • Sign in using your registration or enrollment number and password
  • Once logged in, click on Variation on the dashboard
  • Choose the type of variation from the drop down, write the reason(s) for variation and attach the appropriate evidence
  • Submit and pay if payment is required and wait for communication from the Board on the review process.
